      "message": "I don\u0027t know how I feel about the use of inheritance here. In general, I\u0027m very much in the \"use composition, not inheritance\" camp of the debate. So I guess the question is, what\u0027s inheritance enabling here?\n\nAll the BasicBlock subclasses could instead be composing a BasicBlock and implementing the Block interface (which can maybe be renamed Visitor), and they would mostly look the same (call .basic_block() instead of super().__init__()).\n\nThoughts?",
