      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m mostly in the same camp of preferring composition, but the Visitor pattern pretty much requires inheritance[1]. I\u0027m planning to add type annotations in a later commit (once I have some amount of assurance that it won\u0027t break in the various build systems), and composition wouldn\u0027t cut it here because I would build a huge union type of all the concrete classes :/\n\n\u003e implementing the Block interface (which can maybe be renamed Visitor)\n\ni\u0027m introducing a proper Visitor class in a later commit, so I cannot rename Block.\n\n1: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Visitor_pattern#Structure",
